This paper discusses the potential of neural computation and its impact on computing sciences, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions deep learning and neuromorphic hardware, which are both related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The discussion of materials science and the end of Moore's Law suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the interaction between computing sciences and neurosciences, which could fall under the cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) sub-category.
